<item>
            <title>[CAMEL-5151] camel-netty psuedo proxy</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-5151</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I have a route:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;   from(&quot;netty:tcp://somewhere:1234?...&quot;)&lt;br/&gt;
     .to(&quot;bean:myBean?method=callOut&quot;)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Where the callOut method does several things, followed by a producerTemplate call to another netty endpoint:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;   producerTemplate.sendBody(&quot;netty:tcp://somewhereElse:6789...&quot;, ExchangePattern.InOut, body);&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m unable to proxy &quot;directly&quot; from/to the netty endpoints, and need to pass through this bean.  However, I receive the following exception:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;   Caused by: java.lang.IllegalStateException: await*() in I/O thread causes a dead lock or sudden performance drop. Use addListener()    instead or call await*() from a different thread.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
